Kalam Mekhar|Kalam	A former Claw assassin turned Bridgeburner, towering and deadly with knives, driven by a strict personal honour and loyalty to his squadmates.
Ben Adaephon Delat|Quick Ben|Delat	Mage of the 9th Squad, Bridgeburners, originally from the Seven Cities continent. Black-skinned and tall with a lean face and fine ascetic features, he had a row of neat, smallish, white teeth. His arms were scrawny, and his long hands were almost feminine and also described as thin and spidery. He wore leather armour over a heavy quilted tunic, thin wool undergarments, leather leggings, and moccasins. His voice took on a strange lilt whenever he struggled against speaking his mind. He had a habit of licking his lips when nervous.\n\nWhiskeyjack once stated that while Kruppe might have been the most intelligent man alive, Quick Ben was but a short step behind.
Ganoes Stabro Paran|Ganoes|Paran	A noble-born Malazan officer, eldest son of House Paran of Unta, who became closely tied to the Bridgeburners and later served as Master of the Deck, his fate intertwined with the unit's legacy. Paran was described as having black hair, an easy face to rest eyes upon and a broad back. He wore a helm as part of his uniform and when on the road, wore a travelling cloak.
Toc	<b>Disambiguation:</b><br>• <a href="bword://Toc the Younger">Toc the Younger</a><br>• <a href="bword://Toc the Elder">Toc the Elder</a>
Toc the Younger	A Malazan scout and ally of the Bridgeburners, scarred in body and mind yet fiercely loyal, whose path crossed repeatedly with the squad's fate.
Toc the Elder	The father of Toc the Younger, a legendary warrior of the Malazan Empire.
Bridgeburners	The Bridgeburners were a legendary elite division in the Malazan 2nd Army who were respected by the majority of the Malazan Empire and even their enemies. The unit symbol was a stone arched bridge, lit with ruby flames.\n\n<i>"First in, last out."</i> (Motto of the Bridgeburners)\n\n<i>"A Bridgeburner—such a strange name for soldiers, and yet . . . so perfect there in the chasm between the living and the dead."</i> (Kalyth)
